public abstract class ProposeRequestService<T> extends BaseRepositoryImpl<T>
Abstract base service class for handling proposal request operations. This class provides common functionality for processing change proposals that contain serialized field values which need to be applied to target entities. The service acts as a bridge between the proposal system and actual entity modification by deserializing proposed changes and applying them to business objects using reflection. This enables the system to preview proposed changes and create modified entity versions for administrative review. Subclasses should extend this service to implement specific proposal types such as entity change proposals or user task proposals, while inheriting the common field copying functionality.

    • copyProposeChangeFieldToBusinessClass

      protected void copyProposeChangeFieldToBusinessClass(List<ProposeChangeField> proposeChangeFieldList, Object targetEntity) throws IllegalAccessException, InvocationTargetException, NoSuchMethodException
      Applies proposed field changes to a target business entity. This method processes a list of proposed changes by deserializing each field value and setting it on the target entity using reflection. The operation creates a modified version of the entity that represents what the entity would look like if the proposed changes were applied.
      Each proposed change field contains:
      - The field name to be modified
      - A serialized value representing the proposed new value
      The method deserializes each value and uses Apache Commons PropertyUtils to dynamically set the property on the target entity, enabling type-safe property assignment without compile-time knowledge of the entity structure.
      Parameters:
      proposeChangeFieldList - list of proposed field changes to apply
      targetEntity - the business entity to receive the proposed changes
      Throws:
      IllegalAccessException
      InvocationTargetException
      NoSuchMethodException
